-- Czech Stocks: Vienna Insurance, Fortuna Entertainment Are Active
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-03-22T16:11:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-22/czech-stocks-vienna-insurance-fortuna-entertainment-are-active.html
The Czech Republic’s  PX (PX)  stock index
declined for a third day, retreating 0.2 percent to 990.2 at the
close in Prague.  The following were among the most active  equities  on the
Prague Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Vienna Insurance Group AG (VIG CP) dropped 1.4 percent to
828 koruna, its fourth day of losses. Financial companies were
among the biggest stock decliners in Europe after manufacturing
gauges in the euro area and China declined.  Fortuna Entertainment Group NV (FORTUNA)   increased 0.9
percent to 98.89 koruna after ING Groep NV recommended buying
the Czech bookmaker’s shares as this year’s European soccer
championship and the Olympic Games are set to boost profit at
the company.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in  Prague  at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  